&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;INTERNAL APPLICANTS ONLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span&gt;Swindon Renal Unit is a Satellite Unit of Oxford Kidney Unit and provides an Outpatient Service of Haemodialysis, Peritoneal Dialysis and Renal Clinics for patients in Wiltshire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Swindon Renal Unit is a nurse led unit with a highly motivated team committed to a high quality of service, developing individual potential and continuing education. The unit has strong links with the Oxford Kidney Unit and Oxford Brookes University and Northampton University which enable the educational and professional development of staff. This is a very good and exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and motivated Registered Nurse Band 5 who will be wiling to learn new skills and provide care to haemodialysis patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
